ls
- it basically list all the folders, files, links of the directory the user is in 
root@localhost:/home/calvin# ls
Desktop  Pictures   Music  Videos  Config   


ls -l
- this is more detailed one, still same function but in more detail, like showing if the directory is file, link or folder
root@localhost:/home/calvin# ls -l
total 5
drwxr-xr-x. 2 calvin calvin 6 Feb 23 13:48 Desktop
drwxr-xr-x. 2 calvin calvin 6 Feb 23 13:48 Pictures
drwxr-xr-x. 2 calvin calvin 6 Feb 23 13:48 Music
drwxr-xr-x. 2 calvin calvin 6 Feb 23 13:48 Videos
drwxr-xr-x. 2 calvin calvin 6 Feb 23 13:48 Config

ls -ltr
- this is used for listing all the document but in a specific order. the order is from oldest to newest

ls -lt
- this is used for listing too but the order is from the newest to the oldest



